H3.text: In which African country is Mount Kilimanjaro. TNZ

A4.text: Mount Kilimanjaro is a large dormant volcano in Tanzania.

A5.text: Tanzania is the site of Africa's highest and lowest points: Mount Kilimanjaro, at 5,895 metres (19,341 ft) above sea level, and the floor of Lake Tanganyika, at 1,471 metres (4,826 ft) below sea level, respectively.

A6.text: Tanzania is mountainous and densely forested in the north-east, where Mount Kilimanjaro, the highest mountain in Africa, is located.
